01200 static inline uint64_t CVMX_NPEI_WIN_WR_MASK_FUNC(void)
01201 {
01202     if (!(OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN52XX) || OCTEON_IS_MODEL(OCTEON_CN56XX)))
01203         cvmx_warn("CVMX_NPEI_WIN_WR_MASK not supported on this chip\n");
01204     return 0x0000000000000230ull;
01205 }

01207 #define CVMX_NPEI_WIN_WR_MASK (0x0000000000000230ull)
01208 #endif

01210 /**
01211  * cvmx_npei_bar1_index#
01212  *
01213  * Total Address is 16Kb; 0x0000 - 0x3fff, 0x000 - 0x7fe(Reg, every other 8B)
01214  *
01215  * General  5kb; 0x0000 - 0x13ff, 0x000 - 0x27e(Reg-General)
01216  * PktMem  10Kb; 0x1400 - 0x3bff, 0x280 - 0x77e(Reg-General-Packet)
01217  * Rsvd     1Kb; 0x3c00 - 0x3fff, 0x780 - 0x7fe(Reg-NCB Only Mode)
01218  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_CNT_INT_ENB[PORT]
01219  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_TIME_INT_ENB[PORT]
01220  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_CNT_INT[PORT]
01221  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_TIME_INT[PORT]
01222  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_PCIE_PORT[PP]
01223  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_SLIST_ROR[ROR]
01224  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_SLIST_ROR[NSR] ?
01225  *                                   == NPEI_PKT_SLIST_ES[ES]
01226  *                                   == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BAOFF_DBELL[AOFF]
01227  *                                   == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BAOFF_DBELL[DBELL]
01228  *                                   == NPEI_PKTn_CNTS[CNT]
01229  * NPEI_CTL_STATUS[OUTn_ENB]         == NPEI_PKT_OUT_ENB[ENB]
01230  * NPEI_BASE_ADDRESS_OUTPUTn[BADDR]  == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BADDR[ADDR]
01231  * NPEI_DESC_OUTPUTn[SIZE]           == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_FIFO_RSIZE[RSIZE]
01232  * NPEI_Pn_DBPAIR_ADDR[NADDR]        == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BADDR[ADDR] + NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BAOFF_DBELL[AOFF]
01233  * NPEI_PKT_CREDITSn[PTR_CNT]        == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BAOFF_DBELL[DBELL]
01234  * NPEI_P0_PAIR_CNTS[AVAIL]          == NPEI_PKTn_SLIST_BAOFF_DBELL[DBELL]
01235  * NPEI_P0_PAIR_CNTS[FCNT]           ==
01236  * NPEI_PKTS_SENTn[PKT_CNT]          == NPEI_PKTn_CNTS[CNT]
01237  * NPEI_OUTPUT_CONTROL[Pn_BMODE]     == NPEI_PKT_OUT_BMODE[BMODE]
01238  * NPEI_PKT_CREDITSn[PKT_CNT]        == NPEI_PKTn_CNTS[CNT]
01239  * NPEI_BUFF_SIZE_OUTPUTn[BSIZE]     == NPEI_PKT_SLIST_ID_SIZE[BSIZE]
01240  * NPEI_BUFF_SIZE_OUTPUTn[ISIZE]     == NPEI_PKT_SLIST_ID_SIZE[ISIZE]
01241  * NPEI_OUTPUT_CONTROL[On_CSRM]      == NPEI_PKT_DPADDR[DPTR] & NPEI_PKT_OUT_USE_IPTR[PORT]
01242  * NPEI_OUTPUT_CONTROL[On_ES]        == NPEI_PKT_DATA_OUT_ES[ES]
01243  * NPEI_OUTPUT_CONTROL[On_NS]        == NPEI_PKT_DATA_OUT_NS[NSR] ?
01244  * NPEI_OUTPUT_CONTROL[On_RO]        == NPEI_PKT_DATA_OUT_ROR[ROR]
01245  * NPEI_PKTS_SENT_INT_LEVn[PKT_CNT]  == NPEI_PKT_INT_LEVELS[CNT]
01246  * NPEI_PKTS_SENT_TIMEn[PKT_TIME]    == NPEI_PKT_INT_LEVELS[TIME]
01247  * NPEI_OUTPUT_CONTROL[IPTR_On]      == NPEI_PKT_IPTR[IPTR]
01248  * NPEI_PCIE_PORT_OUTPUT[]           == NPEI_PKT_PCIE_PORT[PP]
01249  *
01250  *                  NPEI_BAR1_INDEXX = NPEI BAR1 IndexX Register
01251  *
01252  * Contains address index and control bits for access to memory ranges of BAR-1. Index is build from supplied address [25:22].
01253  * NPEI_BAR1_INDEX0 through NPEI_BAR1_INDEX15 is used for transactions orginating with PCIE-PORT0 and NPEI_BAR1_INDEX16
01254  * through NPEI_BAR1_INDEX31 is used for transactions originating with PCIE-PORT1.
01255  */
01256 union cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx {
01257     uint32_t u32;
01258     struct cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx_s {
01259 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01260     uint32_t reserved_18_31               : 14;
01261     uint32_t addr_idx                     : 14; /**< Address bits [35:22] sent to L2C */
01262     uint32_t ca                           : 1;  /**< Set '1' when access is not to be cached in L2. */
01263     uint32_t end_swp                      : 2;  /**< Endian Swap Mode */
01264     uint32_t addr_v                       : 1;  /**< Set '1' when the selected address range is valid. */
01265 #else
01266     uint32_t addr_v                       : 1;
01267     uint32_t end_swp                      : 2;
01268     uint32_t ca                           : 1;
01269     uint32_t addr_idx                     : 14;
01270     uint32_t reserved_18_31               : 14;
01271 #endif
01272     } s;
01273     struct cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx_s        cn52xx;
01274     struct cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx_s        cn52xxp1;
01275     struct cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx_s        cn56xx;
01276     struct cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx_s        cn56xxp1;
01277 };
01278 typedef union cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx cvmx_npei_bar1_indexx_t;

01788 /**
01789  * cvmx_npei_ctl_port0
01790  *
01791  * NPEI_CTL_PORT0 = NPEI's Control Port 0
01792  *
01793  * Contains control for access for Port0
01794  */
01795 union cvmx_npei_ctl_port0 {
01796     uint64_t u64;
01797     struct cvmx_npei_ctl_port0_s {
01798 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01799     uint64_t reserved_21_63               : 43;
01800     uint64_t waitl_com                    : 1;  /**< When set '1' casues the NPI to wait for a commit
01801                                                          from the L2C before sending additional completions
01802                                                          to the L2C from the PCIe.
01803                                                          Set this for more conservative behavior. Clear
01804                                                          this for more aggressive, higher-performance
01805                                                          behavior */
01806     uint64_t intd                         : 1;  /**< When '0' Intd wire asserted. Before mapping. */
01807     uint64_t intc                         : 1;  /**< When '0' Intc wire asserted. Before mapping. */
01808     uint64_t intb                         : 1;  /**< When '0' Intb wire asserted. Before mapping. */
01809     uint64_t inta                         : 1;  /**< When '0' Inta wire asserted. Before mapping. */
01810     uint64_t intd_map                     : 2;  /**< Maps INTD to INTA(00), INTB(01), INTC(10) or
01811                                                          INTD (11). */
01812     uint64_t intc_map                     : 2;  /**< Maps INTC to INTA(00), INTB(01), INTC(10) or
01813                                                          INTD (11). */
01814     uint64_t intb_map                     : 2;  /**< Maps INTB to INTA(00), INTB(01), INTC(10) or
01815                                                          INTD (11). */
01816     uint64_t inta_map                     : 2;  /**< Maps INTA to INTA(00), INTB(01), INTC(10) or
01817                                                          INTD (11). */
01818     uint64_t ctlp_ro                      : 1;  /**< Relaxed ordering enable for Completion TLPS. */
01819     uint64_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
01820     uint64_t ptlp_ro                      : 1;  /**< Relaxed ordering enable for Posted TLPS. */
01821     uint64_t bar2_enb                     : 1;  /**< When set '1' BAR2 is enable and will respond when
01822                                                          clear '0' BAR2 access will cause UR responses. */
01823     uint64_t bar2_esx                     : 2;  /**< Value will be XORed with pci-address[37:36] to
01824                                                          determine the endian swap mode. */
01825     uint64_t bar2_cax                     : 1;  /**< Value will be XORed with pcie-address[38] to
01826                                                          determine the L2 cache attribute.
01827                                                          Not cached in L2 if XOR result is 1 */
01828     uint64_t wait_com                     : 1;  /**< When set '1' casues the NPI to wait for a commit
01829                                                          from the L2C before sending additional stores to
01830                                                          the L2C from the PCIe.
01831                                                          Most applications will not notice a difference, so
01832                                                          should not set this bit. Setting the bit is more
01833                                                          conservative on ordering, lower performance */
01834 #else
01835     uint64_t wait_com                     : 1;
01836     uint64_t bar2_cax                     : 1;
01837     uint64_t bar2_esx                     : 2;
01838     uint64_t bar2_enb                     : 1;
01839     uint64_t ptlp_ro                      : 1;
01840     uint64_t reserved_6_6                 : 1;
01841     uint64_t ctlp_ro                      : 1;
01842     uint64_t inta_map                     : 2;
01843     uint64_t intb_map                     : 2;
01844     uint64_t intc_map                     : 2;
01845     uint64_t intd_map                     : 2;
01846     uint64_t inta                         : 1;
01847     uint64_t intb                         : 1;
01848     uint64_t intc                         : 1;
01849     uint64_t intd                         : 1;
01850     uint64_t waitl_com                    : 1;
01851     uint64_t reserved_21_63               : 43;
01852 #endif
01853     } s;
01854     struct cvmx_npei_ctl_port0_s          cn52xx;
01855     struct cvmx_npei_ctl_port0_s          cn52xxp1;
01856     struct cvmx_npei_ctl_port0_s          cn56xx;
01857     struct cvmx_npei_ctl_port0_s          cn56xxp1;
01858 };

01905                                                          conservative on ordering, lower performance */
01906 #else

01913     uint64_t ctlp_ro                      : 1;
01914     uint64_t inta_map                     : 2;
01915     uint64_t intb_map                     : 2;
01916     uint64_t intc_map                     : 2;
01917     uint64_t intd_map                     : 2;
01918     uint64_t inta                         : 1;
01919     uint64_t intb                         : 1;
01920     uint64_t intc                         : 1;
01921     uint64_t intd                         : 1;
01922     uint64_t waitl_com                    : 1;
01923     uint64_t reserved_21_63               : 43;
01924 #endif
01925     } s;

01933 /**
01934  * cvmx_npei_ctl_status
01935  *
01936  * NPEI_CTL_STATUS = NPEI Control Status Register
01937  *
01938  * Contains control and status for NPEI. Writes to this register are not oSrdered with writes/reads to the PCIe Memory space.
01939  * To ensure that a write has completed the user must read the register before making an access(i.e. PCIe memory space)
01940  * that requires the value of this register to be updated.
01941  */
01942 union cvmx_npei_ctl_status {
01943     uint64_t u64;
01944     struct cvmx_npei_ctl_status_s {
01945 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01946     uint64_t reserved_44_63               : 20;
01947     uint64_t p1_ntags                     : 6;  /**< Number of tags avaiable for PCIe Port1.
01948                                                          In RC mode 1 tag is needed for each outbound TLP
01949                                                          that requires a CPL TLP. In Endpoint mode the
01950                                                          number of tags required for a TLP request is
01951                                                          1 per 64-bytes of CPL data + 1.
01952                                                          This field should only be written as part of
01953                                                          reset sequence, before issuing any reads, CFGs, or
01954                                                          IO transactions from the core(s). */
01955     uint64_t p0_ntags                     : 6;  /**< Number of tags avaiable for PCIe Port0.
01956                                                          In RC mode 1 tag is needed for each outbound TLP
01957                                                          that requires a CPL TLP. In Endpoint mode the
01958                                                          number of tags required for a TLP request is
01959                                                          1 per 64-bytes of CPL data + 1.
01960                                                          This field should only be written as part of
01961                                                          reset sequence, before issuing any reads, CFGs, or
01962                                                          IO transactions from the core(s). */
01963     uint64_t cfg_rtry                     : 16; /**< The time x 0x10000 in core clocks to wait for a
01964                                                          CPL to a CFG RD that does not carry a Retry Status.
01965                                                          Until such time that the timeout occurs and Retry
01966                                                          Status is received for a CFG RD, the Read CFG Read
01967                                                          will be resent. A value of 0 disables retries and
01968                                                          treats a CPL Retry as a CPL UR. */
01969     uint64_t ring_en                      : 1;  /**< When '0' forces "relative Q position" received
01970                                                          from PKO to be zero, and replicates the back-
01971                                                          pressure indication for the first ring attached
01972                                                          to a PKO port across all the rings attached to a
01973                                                          PKO port.  When '1' backpressure is on a per
01974                                                          port/ring. */
01975     uint64_t lnk_rst                      : 1;  /**< Set when PCIe Core 0 request a link reset due to
01976                                                          link down state. This bit is only reset on raw
01977                                                          reset so it can be read for state to determine if
01978                                                          a reset occured. Bit is cleared when a '1' is
01979                                                          written to this field. */
01980     uint64_t arb                          : 1;  /**< PCIe switch arbitration mode. '0' == fixed priority
01981                                                          NPEI, PCIe0, then PCIe1. '1' == round robin. */
01982     uint64_t pkt_bp                       : 4;  /**< Unused */
01983     uint64_t host_mode                    : 1;  /**< Host mode */
01984     uint64_t chip_rev                     : 8;  /**< The chip revision. */
01985 #else
01986     uint64_t chip_rev                     : 8;
01987     uint64_t host_mode                    : 1;
01988     uint64_t pkt_bp                       : 4;
01989     uint64_t arb                          : 1;
01990     uint64_t lnk_rst                      : 1;
01991     uint64_t ring_en                      : 1;
01992     uint64_t cfg_rtry                     : 16;
01993     uint64_t p0_ntags                     : 6;
01994     uint64_t p1_ntags                     : 6;
01995     uint64_t reserved_44_63               : 20;
01996 #endif
01997     } s;

02000 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD

02112                                                          POW,   SubId7

02138                                                          MIO,   SubId0
02139                                                          MIO,   SubId7

02142                                                          POW,   SubId1
02143                                                          POW,   SubId2
02144                                                          POW,   SubId3
02145                                                          POW,   SubId7
02146                                                          IPD,   SubId7
02147                                                          USBN0, SubId7 */
02148     uint64_t c1_b1_s                      : 3;  /**< Pcie-Port1, Bar1 Size. 1 == 64MB, 2 == 128MB,
02149                                                          3 == 256MB, 4 == 512MB, 5 == 1024MB, 6 == 2048MB,
02150                                                          0 and 7 are reserved. */

02600                                                          engine. After being enabled a DMA engine should not

02602     uint64_t dma3_enb                     : 1;  /**< DMA# enable. Enables the operation of the DMA

02617                                                          Endian address. */

02625                                                          be returned to when used. */

02627                                                          if '0' then the number of bytes in the dma transfer
02628                                                          will be added to the count register. */
02629     uint64_t o_ro                         : 1;  /**< Relaxed Ordering Mode for DMA. */
02630     uint64_t o_ns                         : 1;  /**< Nosnoop For DMA. */
02631     uint64_t o_es                         : 2;  /**< Endian Swap Mode for DMA. */
02632     uint64_t o_mode                       : 1;  /**< Select PCI_POINTER MODE to be used.
02633                                                          '1' use pointer values for address and register

02793 /**
02794  * cvmx_npei_dma_pcie_req_num
02795  *
02796  * NPEI_DMA_PCIE_REQ_NUM = NPEI DMA PCIE Outstanding Read Request Number
02797  *
02798  * Outstanding PCIE read request number for DMAs and Packet, maximum number is 16
02799  */
02800 union cvmx_npei_dma_pcie_req_num {
02801     uint64_t u64;
02802     struct cvmx_npei_dma_pcie_req_num_s {
02803 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
02804     uint64_t dma_arb                      : 1;  /**< DMA_PKT Read Request Arbitration
02805                                                          - 1: DMA0-4 and PKT are round robin. i.e.
02806                                                              DMA0-DMA1-DMA2-DMA3-DMA4-PKT...
02807                                                          - 0: DMA0-4 are round robin, pkt gets selected
02808                                                              half the time. i.e.
02809                                                              DMA0-PKT-DMA1-PKT-DMA2-PKT-DMA3-PKT-DMA4-PKT... */
02810     uint64_t reserved_53_62               : 10;
02811     uint64_t pkt_cnt                      : 5;  /**< PKT outstanding PCIE Read Request Number for each
02812                                                          PCIe port
02813                                                          When PKT_CNT=x, for each PCIe port, the number
02814                                                          of outstanding PCIe memory space reads by the PCIe
02815                                                          packet input/output will not exceed x.
02816                                                          Valid Number is between 1 and 16 */
02817     uint64_t reserved_45_47               : 3;
02818     uint64_t dma4_cnt                     : 5;  /**< DMA4 outstanding PCIE Read Request Number

02831                                                          When DMA2_CNT=x, the number of outstanding PCIe

02833                                                          will not exceed x.
02834                                                          Valid Number is between 1 and 16 */

02837                                                          When DMA1_CNT=x, the number of outstanding PCIe

02839                                                          will not exceed x.
02840                                                          Valid Number is between 1 and 16 */
02841     uint64_t reserved_13_15               : 3;

02843                                                          When DMA0_CNT=x, the number of outstanding PCIe
02844                                                          memory space reads by the PCIe DMA engine 0
02845                                                          will not exceed x.
02846                                                          Valid Number is between 1 and 16 */
02847     uint64_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
02848     uint64_t dma_cnt                      : 5;  /**< Total outstanding PCIE Read Request Number for each
02849                                                          PCIe port
02850                                                          When DMA_CNT=x, for each PCIe port, the total
02851                                                          number of outstanding PCIe memory space reads
02852                                                          by the PCIe DMA engines and packet input/output
02853                                                          will not exceed x.
02854                                                          Valid Number is between 1 and 16 */
02855 #else

03265  * NPEI_INTERRUPT_A_SUM = NPI Interrupt A Summary Register
03266  *
03267  * Set when an interrupt condition occurs, write '1' to clear. When an interrupt bitin this register is set and
03268  * the cooresponding bit in the NPEI_INT_A_ENB register is set, then NPEI_INT_SUM[61] will be set.
03269  */
03270 union cvmx_npei_int_a_sum {
03271     uint64_t u64;
03272     struct cvmx_npei_int_a_sum_s {
03273 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03274     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
03275     uint64_t pout_err                     : 1;  /**< Set when PKO sends packet data with the error bit
03276                                                          set. */
03277     uint64_t pin_bp                       : 1;  /**< Packet input count has exceeded the WMARK.
03278                                                          See NPEI_PKT_IN_BP */
03279     uint64_t p1_rdlk                      : 1;  /**< PCIe port 1 received a read lock. */
03280     uint64_t p0_rdlk                      : 1;  /**< PCIe port 0 received a read lock. */
03281     uint64_t pgl_err                      : 1;  /**< When a read error occurs on a packet gather list
03282                                                          read this bit is set. */
03283     uint64_t pdi_err                      : 1;  /**< When a read error occurs on a packet data read
03284                                                          this bit is set. */
03285     uint64_t pop_err                      : 1;  /**< When a read error occurs on a packet scatter
03286                                                          pointer pair this bit is set. */
03287     uint64_t pins_err                     : 1;  /**< When a read error occurs on a packet instruction
03288                                                          this bit is set. */
03289     uint64_t dma1_cpl                     : 1;  /**< Set each time any PCIe DMA engine recieves a UR/CA
03290                                                          response from PCIe Port 1 */
03291     uint64_t dma0_cpl                     : 1;  /**< Set each time any PCIe DMA engine recieves a UR/CA
03292                                                          response from PCIe Port 0 */
03293 #else
03294     uint64_t dma0_cpl                     : 1;
03295     uint64_t dma1_cpl                     : 1;
03296     uint64_t pins_err                     : 1;
03297     uint64_t pop_err                      : 1;
03298     uint64_t pdi_err                      : 1;
03299     uint64_t pgl_err                      : 1;
03300     uint64_t p0_rdlk                      : 1;
03301     uint64_t p1_rdlk                      : 1;
03302     uint64_t pin_bp                       : 1;
03303     uint64_t pout_err                     : 1;
03304     uint64_t reserved_10_63               : 54;
03305 #endif
03306     } s;
03307     struct cvmx_npei_int_a_sum_s          cn52xx;
03308     struct cvmx_npei_int_a_sum_cn52xxp1 {
03309 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD

03312                                                          response from PCIe Port 1 */

03319 #endif
03320     } cn52xxp1;

04505  * cvmx_npei_int_info
04506  *
04507  * NPEI_INT_INFO = NPI Interrupt Information
04508  *
04509  * Contains information about some of the interrupt condition that can occur in the NPEI_INTERRUPT_SUM register.
04510  */

04512     uint64_t u64;

04514 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD

04517                                                          is set. This field when set will not change again
04518                                                          unitl NPEI_INTERRUPT_SUM[PIDBOF] is cleared. */
04519     uint64_t psldbof                      : 6;  /**< Field set when the NPEI_INTERRUPT_SUM[PSLDBOF] bit
04520                                                          is set. This field when set will not change again
04521                                                          unitl NPEI_INTERRUPT_SUM[PSLDBOF] is cleared. */
04522 #else
04523     uint64_t psldbof                      : 6;
04524     uint64_t pidbof                       : 6;
04525     uint64_t reserved_12_63               : 52;
04526 #endif
04527     } s;
04528     struct cvmx_npei_int_info_s           cn52xx;
04529     struct cvmx_npei_int_info_s           cn56xx;
04530     struct cvmx_npei_int_info_s           cn56xxp1;
04531 };

05890 /**
05891  * cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt
05892  *
05893  * NPEI_PCIE_CREDIT_CNT = NPEI PCIE Credit Count
05894  *
05895  * Contains the number of credits for the pcie port FIFOs used by the NPEI. This value needs to be set BEFORE PCIe traffic
05896  * flow from NPEI to PCIE Ports starts. A write to this register will cause the credit counts in the NPEI for the two
05897  * PCIE ports to be reset to the value in this register.
05898  */
05899 union cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt {
05900     uint64_t u64;
05901     struct cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt_s {
05902 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05903     uint64_t reserved_48_63               : 16;
05904     uint64_t p1_ccnt                      : 8;  /**< Port1 C-TLP FIFO Credits.
05905                                                          Legal values are 0x25 to 0x80. */
05906     uint64_t p1_ncnt                      : 8;  /**< Port1 N-TLP FIFO Credits.
05907                                                          Legal values are 0x5 to 0x10. */
05908     uint64_t p1_pcnt                      : 8;  /**< Port1 P-TLP FIFO Credits.
05909                                                          Legal values are 0x25 to 0x80. */
05910     uint64_t p0_ccnt                      : 8;  /**< Port0 C-TLP FIFO Credits.
05911                                                          Legal values are 0x25 to 0x80. */
05912     uint64_t p0_ncnt                      : 8;  /**< Port0 N-TLP FIFO Credits.
05913                                                          Legal values are 0x5 to 0x10. */
05914     uint64_t p0_pcnt                      : 8;  /**< Port0 P-TLP FIFO Credits.
05915                                                          Legal values are 0x25 to 0x80. */
05916 #else
05917     uint64_t p0_pcnt                      : 8;
05918     uint64_t p0_ncnt                      : 8;
05919     uint64_t p0_ccnt                      : 8;
05920     uint64_t p1_pcnt                      : 8;
05921     uint64_t p1_ncnt                      : 8;
05922     uint64_t p1_ccnt                      : 8;
05923     uint64_t reserved_48_63               : 16;
05924 #endif
05925     } s;
05926     struct cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt_s    cn52xx;
05927     struct cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt_s    cn56xx;
05928 };
05929 typedef union cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt cvmx_npei_pcie_credit_cnt_t;
05930 
05931 /**
05932  * cvmx_npei_pcie_msi_rcv
05933  *
05934  * NPEI_PCIE_MSI_RCV = NPEI PCIe MSI Receive
05935  *
05936  * Register where MSI writes are directed from the PCIe.
05937  */
05938 union cvmx_npei_pcie_msi_rcv {
05939     uint64_t u64;
05940     struct cvmx_npei_pcie_msi_rcv_s {
05941 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
05942     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
05943     uint64_t intr                         : 8;  /**< A write to this register will result in a bit in
05944                                                          one of the NPEI_MSI_RCV# registers being set.
05945                                                          Which bit is set is dependent on the previously
05946                                                          written using the NPEI_MSI_WR_MAP register or if
05947                                                          not previously written the reset value of the MAP. */
05948 #else
05949     uint64_t intr                         : 8;
05950     uint64_t reserved_8_63                : 56;
05951 #endif
05952     } s;
05953     struct cvmx_npei_pcie_msi_rcv_s       cn52xx;

06587 /**
06588  * cvmx_npei_pkt_input_control
06589  *
06590  * NPEI_PKT_INPUT_CONTROL = NPEI's Packet Input Control
06591  *
06592  * Control for reads for gather list and instructions.
06593  */
06594 union cvmx_npei_pkt_input_control {
06595     uint64_t u64;
06596     struct cvmx_npei_pkt_input_control_s {
06597 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
06598     uint64_t reserved_23_63               : 41;
06599     uint64_t pkt_rr                       : 1;  /**< When set '1' the input packet selection will be
06600                                                          made with a Round Robin arbitration. When '0'
06601                                                          the input packet ring is fixed in priority,
06602                                                          where the lower ring number has higher priority. */
06603     uint64_t pbp_dhi                      : 13; /**< Field when in [PBP] is set to be used in
06604                                                          calculating a DPTR. */
06605     uint64_t d_nsr                        : 1;  /**< Enables '1' NoSnoop for reading of
06606                                                          gather data. */
06607     uint64_t d_esr                        : 2;  /**< The Endian-Swap-Mode for reading of
06608                                                          gather data. */
06609     uint64_t d_ror                        : 1;  /**< Enables '1' Relaxed Ordering for reading of
06610                                                          gather data. */
06611     uint64_t use_csr                      : 1;  /**< When set '1' the csr value will be used for
06612                                                          ROR, ESR, and NSR. When clear '0' the value in
06613                                                          DPTR will be used. In turn the bits not used for
06614                                                          ROR, ESR, and NSR, will be used for bits [63:60]
06615                                                          of the address used to fetch packet data. */
06616     uint64_t nsr                          : 1;  /**< Enables '1' NoSnoop for reading of
06617                                                          gather list and gather instruction. */
06618     uint64_t esr                          : 2;  /**< The Endian-Swap-Mode for reading of
06619                                                          gather list and gather instruction. */
06620     uint64_t ror                          : 1;  /**< Enables '1' Relaxed Ordering for reading of
06621                                                          gather list and gather instruction. */
06622 #else
06623     uint64_t ror                          : 1;
06624     uint64_t esr                          : 2;
06625     uint64_t nsr                          : 1;
06626     uint64_t use_csr                      : 1;
06627     uint64_t d_ror                        : 1;
06628     uint64_t d_esr                        : 2;
06629     uint64_t d_nsr                        : 1;
06630     uint64_t pbp_dhi                      : 13;
06631     uint64_t pkt_rr                       : 1;
06632     uint64_t reserved_23_63               : 41;
06633 #endif
06634     } s;
06635     struct cvmx_npei_pkt_input_control_s  cn52xx;
06636     struct cvmx_npei_pkt_input_control_s  cn56xx;
06637 };

07070     uint64_t spx0                         : 1;  /**< Always reads as zero */

07073     uint64_t usb1                         : 1;  /**< Always reads as zero */

07076     uint64_t pow                          : 1;  /**< POW_ECC_ERR */
07077     uint64_t tim                          : 1;  /**< TIM_REG_ERROR */

07081     uint64_t zip                          : 1;  /**< ZIP_ERROR */
07082     uint64_t dfa                          : 1;  /**< Always reads as zero */
07083     uint64_t fpa                          : 1;  /**< FPA_INT_SUM */
07084     uint64_t key                          : 1;  /**< KEY_INT_SUM */
07085     uint64_t npei                         : 1;  /**< NPEI_INT_SUM */
07086     uint64_t gmx1                         : 1;  /**< GMX1_RX*_INT_REG & GMX1_TX_INT_REG */
07087     uint64_t gmx0                         : 1;  /**< GMX0_RX*_INT_REG & GMX0_TX_INT_REG */
07088     uint64_t mio                          : 1;  /**< MIO_BOOT_ERR */
07089 #else
07090     uint64_t mio                          : 1;
07091     uint64_t gmx0                         : 1;
07092     uint64_t gmx1                         : 1;
07093     uint64_t npei                         : 1;
07094     uint64_t key                          : 1;
07095     uint64_t fpa                          : 1;

07116     uint64_t lmc1                         : 1;
07117     uint64_t iob                          : 1;

07246 /**

07249  * NPEI_WIN_RD_ADDR = NPEI Window Read Address Register
07250  *
07251  * The address to be read when the NPEI_WIN_RD_DATA register is read.
07252  */
07253 union cvmx_npei_win_rd_addr {
07254     uint64_t u64;
07255     struct cvmx_npei_win_rd_addr_s {
07256 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
07257     uint64_t reserved_51_63               : 13;
07258     uint64_t ld_cmd                       : 2;  /**< The load command sent wit hthe read.
07259                                                          0x0 == Load 8-bytes, 0x1 == Load 4-bytes,
07260                                                          0x2 == Load 2-bytes, 0x3 == Load 1-bytes, */
07261     uint64_t iobit                        : 1;  /**< A 1 or 0 can be written here but this will always
07262                                                          read as '0'. */
07263     uint64_t rd_addr                      : 48; /**< The address to be read from. Whenever the LSB of
07264                                                          this register is written, the Read Operation will
07265                                                          take place.
07266                                                          [47:40] = NCB_ID
07267                                                          [39:0]  = Address
07268                                                          When [47:43] == NPI & [42:0] == 0 bits [39:0] are:
07269                                                               [39:32] == x, Not Used
07270                                                               [31:27] == RSL_ID
07271                                                               [12:0]  == RSL Register Offset */
07272 #else
07273     uint64_t rd_addr                      : 48;
07274     uint64_t iobit                        : 1;
07275     uint64_t ld_cmd                       : 2;
07276     uint64_t reserved_51_63               : 13;
07277 #endif
07278     } s;
07279     struct cvmx_npei_win_rd_addr_s        cn52xx;
07280     struct cvmx_npei_win_rd_addr_s        cn52xxp1;

07312  *

07314  *
07315  * Contains the address to be writen to when a write operation is started by writing the
07316  * NPEI_WIN_WR_DATA register (see below).
07317  *
07318  * Notes:
07319  * Even though address bit [2] can be set, it should always be kept to '0'.
07320  *
07321  */

07328                                                          read as '0'. */
07329     uint64_t wr_addr                      : 46; /**< The address that will be written to when the
07330                                                          NPEI_WIN_WR_DATA register is written.
07331                                                          [47:40] = NCB_ID
07332                                                          [39:3]  = Address
07333                                                          When [47:43] == NPI & [42:0] == 0 bits [39:0] are:
07334                                                               [39:32] == x, Not Used
07335                                                               [31:27] == RSL_ID
07336                                                               [12:2]  == RSL Register Offset
07337                                                               [1:0]   == x, Not Used */
07338     uint64_t reserved_0_1                 : 2;
07339 #else
07340     uint64_t reserved_0_1                 : 2;

07343     uint64_t reserved_49_63               : 15;
07344 #endif
07345     } s;

07405 /**

07409  *
07410  * The name of this register is misleading. The timeout value is used for BAR0 access from PCIE0 and PCIE1.
07411  * Any access to the regigisters on the RML will timeout as 0xFFFF clock cycle. At time of timeout the next
07412  * RML access will start, and interrupt will be set, and in the case of reads no data will be returned.
07413  *
07414  * The value of this register should be set to a minimum of 0x200000 to ensure that a timeout to an RML register
07415  * occurs on the RML 0xFFFF timer before the timeout for a BAR0 access from the PCIE#.
07416  */
07417 union cvmx_npei_window_ctl {
07418     uint64_t u64;
07419     struct cvmx_npei_window_ctl_s {
07420 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
07421     uint64_t reserved_32_63               : 32;
07422     uint64_t time                         : 32; /**< Time to wait in core clocks to wait for a
07423                                                          BAR0 access to completeon the NCB
07424                                                          before timing out. A value of 0 will cause no
07425                                                          timeouts. A minimum value of 0x200000 should be
07426                                                          used when this register is not set to 0x0. */
07427 #else
07428     uint64_t time                         : 32;
07429     uint64_t reserved_32_63               : 32;
07430 #endif
07431     } s;
07432     struct cvmx_npei_window_ctl_s         cn52xx;
07433     struct cvmx_npei_window_ctl_s         cn52xxp1;
07434     struct cvmx_npei_window_ctl_s         cn56xx;
07435     struct cvmx_npei_window_ctl_s         cn56xxp1;
07436 };
